    COMPUNET TODAY:  15th DECEMBER 198989

 NETWORKACCESSS
 We have been negotiating with  Dialcom
 (Prestel-Gold-Micronet)  for access via
the  Prestel Network . They want to charge
everyone a  Prestel  subscription in addi-
tion to the  Compunet  Sub. We are contin-
uing talking but it looks like it may
take a while.

Therefore, earlier this week we reopened
talks with  Fastrak  (the Midland Bank
network). They have 88 access points
(including Dublin) at 1200/75 and a high
speed (upto 2400 baud and MNP level 6!).
 Level 6 gives 4800 baud with Data Compr-
ession Tricom network.  Charges would be
same for all speeds.

I hope for more news next week but a lot
of people at  Fastrak  will be on holiday
over Christmas and new year.
    Nick Green 

